TERRAFORM MODULES : 
A module is a container for related resources that are used together. They are the primary way to package & reuse configurations.

Parent & child module :
A parent (calling) module references and configures other modules, while a child module is the reusable infrastructure component being called.
Modules can be retrieved from a registry, a repo or stored locally

MODULE VERSIONING:
module "prod-vpc" {
  source = path
  version = "5.12.0"     //terraform init -upgrade

  name = var.vpc_name
  cidr = var.vpc_cidr_block

  azs = ["us-west-2a", "us-west-2b"]
  private_subnets = ["10.0.1.0/24"]
  public_subnets = ["10.0.2.0/24"]

  enable_nat_gateway = true
  single_nat_gateway = true
}

By default, the root module doesnot have access to data/variables in the child module
After adding module to config file, run terraform init.
